-- plugins known to leave behind significant wp_options rows, WP-Cron events,
-- or custom tables when deactivated/deleted. A full top-3000 regeneration is
-- a documented offline follow-up (see tools/corpus-gen/README.md).
--
-- Patterns are RE2-compatible anchored regexps or plain string literals.
-- Exact literals (no regexp metacharacters) classify as ConfidenceExact.
-- Anchored prefix patterns (^prefix_) classify as ConfidencePrefix.
--
-- SECURITY INVARIANT — minimum prefix body length:
-- Anchored prefix patterns (^X_) must have at least 4 characters before the first
-- underscore. Short prefixes like ^et_, ^ep_, ^lp_, ^ls_, ^kb_, ^vc_, ^nf_,
-- ^bp_, ^gf_, ^rg_, ^fm_, ^ac_, ^um_, ^ct_ are too ambiguous: a 2–3 character
-- root matches unrelated option names from foreign plugins and could cause
-- false-confidence misclassification in future P3.8 deletion paths. Short
-- prefixes that previously appeared in this seed have been either replaced by
-- the longer co-prefix already present in the same corpus row (e.g. ^ep_ →
-- ^elasticpress_, ^um_ → ^ultimate_member_, ^lp_ → ^learnpress_) or removed
-- and demoted to heuristic-only (slug-normalization match, never deletion-eligible).
-- The corpus-gen tool enforces this same 4-char floor at generation time via
-- minPrefixBodyLen = 4.
--
-- The seed runs as the schema owner (not wpmgr_app). The owner bypasses ENABLE
-- RLS (not FORCE) so these INSERTs succeed without an explicit INSERT policy.
-- wpmgr_app has SELECT only (REVOKE applied in 20260605000000_m40_plugin_signatures.sql).
